><subfield code='b'>paper ;</subfield><subfield code='c'>240 x 160 (180 x 112) mm. bound to 244 x 175 mm.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Ms. codex.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Title from title page (fol. 2a).</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='520'><subfield code='a'>Amplification (takhmīs) of the Muʻallaqāt by ʻAlāʼ al-Dīn ʻAlī ibn Shams al-Dīn al-Mūsawī al-Ṭūsī [ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad Ibn Daftarkhān].</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>15 lines per page. Written in medium large naskh in black ink, with larger script for headings. Light cream glazed paper. The paper has been frame-ruled. Simply illuminated title page (ʻunwān) in gold, green and blue. Leaves wanting between fol. 2 and 3. Collation notes (see fol. 6b). Foliation in pencil using Arabic numerals. Foliation in pencil using Western numerals.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Lacuna after fol. 2. The first complete poem begins on fol. 6b (Qaṣīdat Ṭarafah ibn al-ʻAbd al-Wāʼilī).</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>The date Rabīʻ al-Awwal 655 [1257] in the colophon (fol. 70a) seems to be the date of completion of the text. See Mach, R. Yahuda.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='561'><subfield code='a'>Reading statements on fol. 1a, 70b, 71a. Ownership statements on fol. 1b, 2a (dated Ṣafar 723 [1323]). Seal on fol. 2b. Waqf (see fol. 7b-8a). Acquired from Abraham Shalom Yahuda, 1942.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='563'><subfield code='a'>Upper and lower covers and envelope flap in light brown leather stamped? with blue, red and green ink. The upper and lower covers have the same blind-stamped corner pieces and central mandorla. The envelope flap has a portion of the same mandorla on its pointe. Decorated red paper pastedowns and endleaves.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='4' ind2=' ' tag='510'><subfield code='a'>Mach, R. Yahuda,</subfield><subfield code='c'>4239</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='4' ind2=' ' tag='510'><subfield code='a'>Brockelmann, C. GAL,</subfield><subfield code='c'>SI, 36</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='541'><subfield code='c'>Gift ;</subfield><subfield code='a'>Robert Garrett, Class of 1897 ;</subfield><subfield code='d'>1942.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='0' tag='630'><subfield code='a'>Muʻallaqāt.</subfield><subfield code='0'>http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79127139</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='0' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Arabic poetry</subfield><subfield code='y'>13th century.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='0' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Manuscripts, Arabic</subfield><subfield code='z'>New Jersey</subfield><subfield code='z'>Princeton.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Manuscripts, Arabic</subfield><subfield code='y'>13th century.</subfield><subfield code='2'>lcsh</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Illuminated title pages</subfield><subfield code='z'>Islamic Empire</subfield><subfield code='y'>13th century.</subfield><subfield code='2'>local</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Illuminated manuscripts</subfield><subfield code='z'>Islamic Empire</subfield><subfield code='y'>13th century.</subfield><subfield code='2'>aat</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Waqf</subfield><subfield code='x'>Books</subfield><subfield code='2'>lcsh.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='4' ind2='1' tag='856'><subfield code='u'>http://arks.princeton.edu/ark:/88435/9593tv194</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2=' ' tag='880'><subfield code='6'>100-01/r</subfield><subfiel